RS on Unshakable Determination to Defend Korean Style�@Socialism to Last 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The Korean People's Army and people will as ever regard the idea and faith of Juche as an eternal lifeline and dynamically make a long journey of the Songun revolution despite any storm and stress, united close around leader Kim Jong Il, Rodong Sinmun Monday says in a signed article. It goes on:
 The faith of the Korean people is characterized by the firm belief that the path of independence and socialism taken by them is entirely just, their steadfast resolve not to step back even a bit from this road of their own choice and their sincerest desire to hold President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il in high esteem without any vacillation under any changed situation and in any adversity. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people's faith being fully displayed in the Songun era represents the noble thought based on the absolute trust in Kim Jong Il and their pride and self-esteem of having a great history, traditions and a wealth of experience in struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The revolutionary traits of the Korean people strong in idea and faith find a vivid manifestation in that they share their will and destiny with their leader on the road of the Songun revolution and display their patriotic enthusiasm to the full in building a rich and powerful nation with pure conscience and sense of obligation. These traits also find their expression in that they are resolutely defending Korean style socialism with transparent spirit of anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Neither honeyed words nor horror strategy on the part of the U.S. imperialists can ever work on the Korean people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They are not such type of people who will desert the road of socialism, the path of Juche, in any storm. The U.S. imperialists are resorting to all sorts of despicable moves to bring down the system in the DPRK by destabilizing its society. But nothing can shake the determination and faith of its army and people to defend to the last Korean style socialism, their destiny and lifeline, from a transparent view of anti-imperialist struggle. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The evermore undisguised moves of the U.S. imperialists to destroy socialism in the DPRK will only reinforce the determination and will of its army and people to finally settle accounts with the enemy and defend their ideology, system and cause to the last.

Koguryo, Pride of Korean Nation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The registration of mural paintings in Koguryo tombs as world cultural heritage is giving a great pride to the entire Korean people in the north, south and overseas.
 Koguryo (277 B.C.-668 A.D.) was the most powerful state in the Korean history. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was the first feudal state built in Korea by the descendants of the ancient Korean tribe. It, covering a vast territory, created an advanced economy and culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Its territory extended 2,400 kilometers from east to west and 1,600 kilometers from north to south in the late 5th century and in the early 6th century. It was as large as ten times the whole territories of Paekje, Silla and Kaya. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo could become a powerful country mainly because of its people's strong sense of patriotism and their attaching a great importance to the military. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to a legend about the building of Koguryo, King Tongmyong, the founder of the country, was called Jumong as he had been very good in archery from his childhood.
 At that time, each village had a Kyongdang (school) where unmarried young people learned how to read and write and trained military arts. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Bravery and military arts were important things in personnel affairs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Koguryo people, with a high sense of pride and brave mettle, had nothing to do with flunkeyism and submission and defended the honor of the nation and the sovereignty of the country with credit for nearly 1,000 years, repulsing the millions of aggressors. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For several centuries before and after Christ, the feudal relationship was consolidated and developed and a regular feudal system was set up in Koguryo. It had a great influence on the state and social system of the neighboring countries which appeared later. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo achieved a rapid development in the field of culture, too. It became one of the most developed countries in Asia and a civilized state with advanced culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The mural paintings of Koguryo on dresses show that the dressing system of Koguryo greatly contributed to the development of the nation's costume. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The unique under-floor heating system of the Korean people was further developed in that period and the nation's inherent style of architecture has developed on the basis of the advanced architecture of Koguryo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The culture of Koguryo had an influence on neighboring countries, especially on the establishment and development of ancient culture of Japan.

Jonghyang-branded Luster Paint Made in DPRK
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The Korea Rakwon External Technology Service Center of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea produces pearl-like luster paint.
 The Jonghyang-branded paint is made with highly water-proof synthetic resin as an additive. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is used to paint interior and exterior walls and ceilings of public and dwelling buildings. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Painted on the surface of concrete, wooden board, strawboard and vinyl wallpaper, it neither crack nor loosen as it has a strong adhesive power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, with a high pyrogenic and adsorbent nature, is also strong in rust-proofing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One kilogram of Jonghyang is enough to paint two-three square meters. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It has found its way to Malaysia and various other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jong Jong Gun, chief of the center, told KCNA that the center produces various painting materials including ordinary exterior and interior, rust-proof, anti-foul, oil-proof, acid resistant painting materials and oil painting materials according to orders.

Famous Mansudae Art Troupe
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 27 (KCNA) -- The Mansudae Art Troupe of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea has been well known at home and abroad for its artistic activities.
 The art troupe, founded on September 27, 1969, has earned fame for the creation of unique instrumental music pieces from the beginning of its foundation. Typical of them are Kayagum sole "Spring in the Outpost" accompanied by the mixed orchestra and women instrumental ensemble "It Snows". 
 It also created such masterpieces as group dances "Azalea of the Fatherland" and "Glow over Kangson". They well combine beautiful, delicate and rich dancing rhythms, group ensemble, individual technique with each other and organically unify dance with music and stage art. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art troupe sang "Song of General Kim Il Sung" on a high level befitting the national treasure, and created the story of music and dance "Song of Paradise" as a model of combined stage art pieces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The merited men chorus and women chorus are popular in the country for their singing well songs of various themes and folk songs to suit the emotional feelings of the people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The merited women instrumental ensemble with a great arrangement ability, technical skill, unique artistic description and music tradition, is a pride of the art troupe. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through its performances in other countries, it has demonstrated the features of Korean art and made a positive contribution to cementing friendship and solidarity with world progressive people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It, with a lot of People's and Merited Artistes, is distinguishing itself in creating Juche-based art including music and dance pieces.
